author: Chris Boyette and Darran Simon, CNN
description: A pilot and co-pilot aboard a Learjet that crashed Monday afternoon near Teterboro Airport were "missing," Carlstadt Mayor Craig Lahullier said.
title: 2 'missing' in Teterboro Airport crash

author: Spencer Kent | NJ Advance Media for NJ.com
description: A LearJet crashed in an industrial area of Carlstadt just short of the runway at Teterboro Airport on Monday afternoon, killing two crew members.
title: 2 dead as jet crashes on approach to Teterboro

author: Lucy Clarke-Billings
description: The Federal Aviation Administration said a Learjet 35 crashed about a quarter of a mile shy of Teterboro Airport in New Jersey
title: Two dead as small plane crashes into residential area near US airport

author: Daniel Trotta
description: A small plane crashed on its approach to Teterboro Airport in New Jersey on Monday, killing two pilots and sparking fires that could be seen from New York, the Federal Aviation Administration and police said.
title: Learjet crashes on approach to New Jersey airport, killing two pilots

author: DAVID PORTER
description: MOONACHIE, N.J. (AP) â€” A deadly jet crash at a small airport outside New York City has dredged up dormant fears among residents who live within yards of where corporate jets take off and land. A Learjet approaching Teterboro Airport smashed into an industrial area Monday afternoon, killing two crew members and damaging buildings. No one on the ground was injured. Federal investigators are scheduled to give an update on the crash Tuesday. Residents of a community of trailer homes that sits across a street from the end of one of Teterboro's runways are accustomed to the sound of planes taking off and landing.
title: Deadly jet crash renews old fears for residents near airport
